info.p:
                            you could define a hashtable "myGotoHash" and apply it to the attribute
                            
<%
Hashtable myGotoHash = null;
if(request.getParameter("goto")!=null) {
       myGotoHash = new Hashtable();
       myGotoHash.put("id",request.getParameter("goto"));
}
%>                          


<db:form table="customer" followUp="customer.jsp" 
         gotoHt="<%= myGotoHash %>" >
         ... some code ...
</db:form>

hint: the class java.text.DateFormat is a ready-to-use Date formatter.
you can aquire an instance of DateFormat by writing:
DateFormat df = DateFormat.getDateInstance(DateFormat.SHORT);
